🚀 Features
🔎 Password Strength Analyzer

Users can enter a password and instantly receive:

Security Level
Visual Meter
Percentage Score
Suggestions

Example:

Password:
hello123

Strength:
Medium (60%)

Suggestions:
• Add uppercase letters
• Add special characters
🔐 Smart Password Generator

Generate passwords using:

✅ Custom Length (8–20)

✅ Numbers

✅ Uppercase Letters

✅ Special Symbols

Example:

Length:
16

Generated:

P@6M#xL8!tV2kQ3
📊 Visual Progress Meter

Unlike terminal tools, GUI provides:

Weak
████░░░░░░

Medium
██████░░░░

Strong
██████████

This creates better user experience.

👁 Password Visibility Toggle

Users can:

☑ Show Password

Useful for:

Reducing typing mistakes
Password validation
User convenience
📋 Copy Password Feature

Generated password can be copied instantly.

No manual selection required.

🧠 Core Logic Used

This project uses Rule-Based Password Evaluation Logic.

No external APIs.

No machine learning.

Fast and lightweight.

Rule 1 → Length Validation
if len(password) >= 8:
Why?

Long passwords:

Increase entropy
Resist brute-force attacks
Improve security
Rule 2 → Uppercase Detection
[A-Z]

Checks:

Password

instead of

password
Rule 3 → Lowercase Detection
[a-z]

Creates mixed character combinations.

Rule 4 → Numeric Validation
\d

Example:

hello

↓

hello123
Rule 5 → Special Character Detection
!@#$%^&*

Example:

Pass123

↓

P@ss#123
⚙ How Strength Is Calculated
Condition	Score
Length ≥ 8	+1
Uppercase	+1
Lowercase	+1
Number	+1
Special Character	+1

Final Classification:

0–2 → Weak

3–4 → Medium

5 → Strong
